{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-90e","title":"File filtering: binary denylist + wire up .wdpkrignore","description":"Two issues: (1) Binary files like .png are attempted and fail with 'stream did not contain valid UTF-8'. Add a built-in denylist of binary/media extensions (png, jpg, gif, pdf, wasm, zip, tar, etc.) to skip before read. (2) .wdpkrignore is created by wdpkr init but never actually read during indexing — wire it into the ignore::WalkBuilder via add_ignore().","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"tlugger","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:26Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:39Z","started_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:39Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-e11","title":"Cross-file parallelism: wire up --concurrency","description":"The --concurrency flag is parsed but not implemented. Wire it to tokio::sync::Semaphore so N files process concurrently. Summarization is the bottleneck (sequential Anthropic API calls per symbol), so cross-file concurrency should give 4-8x speedup.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"tlugger","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:07Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:38Z","started_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:38Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-wf1","title":"Indexer observability: per-file progress and timing","description":"Add per-file progress output during indexing. Show [N/total] file path (symbols) with per-step timing (summarize, embed, upsert). Running totals at end: elapsed, API calls, files processed/failed/skipped.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"tlugger","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T20:59:59Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-14T21:33:11Z","started_at":"2026-05-14T21:00:38Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T21:33:11Z","close_reason":"Per-file progress with timing (summarize, embed) and running totals (processed, skipped, failed) printed to stderr","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"megagrep-lua","title":"Rewrite Turbopuffer adapter from v1 to v2 API","description":"Our Turbopuffer adapter sends v1 request bodies to v2 URL paths, causing 'cannot set v1 fields in a v2 request' errors. Every operation needs updating: upsert (upsert_rows, flattened attrs, distance_metric), query (rank_by, limit, array filters, rows response), delete (main endpoint, not /delete), namespace probe. Full rewrite of all HTTP types and trait implementations.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"notnottyler","owner":"notnottyler@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T16:28:15Z","created_by":"notnottyler","updated_at":"2026-05-14T16:35:26Z","started_at":"2026-05-14T16:28:21Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T16:35:26Z","close_reason":"Adapter fully rewritten to v2 API spec","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"megagrep-t6k","title":"Interactive config init + API keys in config file","description":"Make config init interactive (prompt for provider/model/keys per section). Store API keys in config file alongside provider settings (env vars still override). Use provider-specific key names in YAML (voyage_api_key, not api_key) so swapping providers doesn't confuse credentials.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"notnottyler@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T15:12:31Z","created_by":"notnottyler","updated_at":"2026-05-14T16:17:18Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T16:17:18Z","close_reason":"Shipped in PR #25 (interactive config init + API keys in config file)","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"megagrep-4jx","title":"--dry-run mode: estimate tokens and cost without API calls","description":"Index dry-run should walk the repo, chunk all files, estimate token counts for summarization + embedding, calculate cost per provider rate, and report totals — without making any API calls or writing to the store. Zero tokens spent.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"notnottyler@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-14T14:41:48Z","created_by":"notnottyler","updated_at":"2026-05-14T15:27:55Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T15:27:55Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-389","title":"search: surface calls/called_by in search results","description":"Include calls and called_by in SearchReport JSON output and --pretty rendering. When null (not yet indexed), render as 'unknown' or omit from JSON (skip_serializing_if). When Some(vec![]), render as empty. For --terse, omit call graph entirely (keep it minimal). For --pretty, show as indented list under each symbol. This gives agents the blast-radius signal without follow-up rg queries.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:13Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:13Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"wdpkr-389","depends_on_id":"wdpkr-blb","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-19T14:44:22Z","created_by":"tlugger","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-blb","title":"indexer: resolve cross-file call edges at index time","description":"After chunking all files, build a symbol table (name → file_path + symbol_id) and resolve the raw outbound-call identifiers from the chunk phase into qualified references. Populate calls (outbound from this symbol) and called_by (inbound — other symbols that reference this one) on each VectorDocument before upsert. Resolution is best-effort: unresolved identifiers (stdlib, external deps, dynamic dispatch) are silently dropped. Incremental index only updates edges for changed files; stale edges from deleted symbols get cleaned up.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:10Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:10Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"wdpkr-blb","depends_on_id":"wdpkr-da4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-19T14:44:21Z","created_by":"tlugger","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"wdpkr-blb","depends_on_id":"wdpkr-qcw","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-19T14:44:20Z","created_by":"tlugger","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":2,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-da4","title":"store: add calls/called_by fields to vector documents","description":"Add optional calls and called_by fields to VectorDocument and SearchResult. Use Option\u003cVec\u003cString\u003e\u003e (not Vec\u003cString\u003e) so null means 'not yet indexed with call-graph data' while Some(vec![]) means 'this symbol genuinely has no callers/callees'. This distinction prevents agents from assuming a symbol is a leaf node when it was just indexed before call-graph support existed. Update Turbopuffer attribute schema, mock store, and serialization.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:09Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:09Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-qcw","title":"chunk: extract call-graph edges from tree-sitter AST","description":"During tree-sitter chunking, extract two sets of identifiers per symbol: (1) outbound calls — function/method calls and type references in the symbol body, (2) symbol's own qualified name for cross-referencing. These are raw identifiers, not resolved — resolution happens at index time by joining against the symbol table. Store as Vec\u003cString\u003e on the chunk output struct. This is the foundation for caller/callee metadata on vector documents.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"tlugger","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-19T20:44:08Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-19T20:46:16Z","started_at":"2026-05-19T20:46:16Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"wdpkr-6ol","title":"search: add --terse flag for compact output","description":"Compact output mode: paths + one-line summaries, no symbols. Composes with --pretty. Truncates summaries to first sentence.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"tlugger","owner":"tyler@dayforward.com","created_at":"2026-05-19T20:19:37Z","created_by":"tlugger","updated_at":"2026-05-19T20:30:11Z","started_at":"2026-05-19T20:26:52Z","closed_at":"2026-05-19T20:30:11Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"wdpkr-6ol","depends_on_id":"wdpkr-pb6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-19T14:19:43Z","created_by":"tlugger","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
